div.p:
10. For if in their Religions, there be no true authoritie spirituall, or iurisdiction, deriued by ordinarie means, and succession from Christ; 
         Important consequences.
       then are they awry in all, nor haue they any true authority, to preach, administer Sacraments, absolue, or bind from sinnes, iudge of doctrine, determine or decree of any spirituall action whatsoeuer; nor are they within the compasse of Christs Church, or state of saluation, as by necessarie consequence doth ensue; and the like of the Catholickes, if they in this point be amisse
